Happy path: return collectorResult with collectorDecision.decisionType = ADVANCE_PHASE and requestedPhase = "TICKETS".
If you believe planning is insufficient, follow the Route-Back Review Protocol:
in your structured JSON response, return a result with only `interruptRequest` populated, explaining the planning gaps.
After review, if approved: set collectorResult with ROUTE_BACK so planning runs again.
After review, if rejected: set collectorResult with ADVANCE_PHASE and requestedPhase = "TICKETS",
filling in finalizedTickets and dependencyGraph with the best available plan.
Only set contextManagerRequest when you need specific missing context from another agent chat/history.
